research_municipality_step.notes: Hickory Creek, TX operates under a mayor/council form of government and is a Type A General Law City. The Town Council consists of a Mayor and five Councilmembers, all elected at-large. Paul Kenney holds the role of Mayor Pro Tem in addition to being a Council Member. While one source listed Richard Dupree for Place 2, the official town website and recent meeting minutes indicate Nick Wohr as the current Councilmember for Place 2.
